rgin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Not being specifically stated in the WB Safeguards Policy, the concerns of persons with disabilities are not considered in the environmental and social safeguards evaluation of the project. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:107%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">All documents related to this project that are available on the World Bank website do not mention anything about persons with disabilities. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:107%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Time and again, projects such as this that do not consider concerns of persons with disabilities will fail to be inclusive. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:107%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The post-2015 MDG transformative shifts include “leave no one behind”, not a sector nor a person. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:107%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We believe that persons with disabilities themselves should represent the sector in all stages of World Bank programs and projects, from formulation down to monitoring and evaluation. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:107%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We believe that the United Kingdom has a vital role to play in seeing to it that the World Bank always protects the rights, and considers the needs, of persons with disabilities in all its programs and projects whenever and wherever applicable.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Benjamin S. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bernandino</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> is a 42-year-old quadriplegic male. He is the Secretary-General of Life Haven, Inc. and a Peer </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Counselor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the Life Haven Independent Living </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Center</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in Valenzuela City, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Phuilippines</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Life Haven is a nongovernmental organization registered in the Philippines. We are guided by the Independent Living Philosophy, teaching and sharing this to others as part of our active participation in the Independent Living Movement. We envision a society where people with disabilities are independent, self-determined and participate actively in promoting self-development. It is our mission to lead the establishment of Independent Living </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">centers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the Philippines as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">avehicle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> towards full empowerment, integration and participation in the community. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Life Haven serves as the Asia regional focal point for the Disability and World Bank Safeguards Campaign, a partnership between the Bank Information </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Center</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Lebanese Physical Handicapped Union, which is working to ensure that the World Bank adopts a systematically inclusive approach to its engagement in developing countries. We are actively advocating to ensure that the World Bank integrates disability into its safeguard policies, which are currently under review. As a major shareholder of the World Bank, it is paramount that the United Kingdom works with the World Bank to improve the inclusiveness of its work. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-indent:36pt"><